PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This note critically analyzes the conditions for equilibrium existence in a model involving incentive schemes and inventory management. It identifies a technical flaw where equilibrium is asserted to exist under certain parameter values when, in fact, it does not. However, by introducing a reasonable assumption that inventory can only be ordered in sufficiently large increments, the qualitative outcomes and key insights remain intact.This paper was accepted by Jeannette Song, operations management.Supplemental Material: The online appendix is available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2023.03914.
AB  - This note critically analyzes the conditions for equilibrium existence in a model involving incentive schemes and inventory management. It identifies a technical flaw where equilibrium is asserted to exist under certain parameter values when, in fact, it does not. However, by introducing a reasonable assumption that inventory can only be ordered in sufficiently large increments, the qualitative outcomes and key insights remain intact.This paper was accepted by Jeannette Song, operations management.Supplemental Material: The online appendix is available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2023.03914.
